00:00:10.920 --> 00:00:12.200
Build it

00:00:12.200 --> 00:00:18.210
Tom Miller built a personal train track that
runs around his nearly 20 acre property. It

00:00:18.210 --> 00:00:21.210
has handmade steam locomotives, 11,000 feet
of track, 30 ft tall railroad trestle, and&nbsp;a

00:00:21.210 --> 00:00:25.510
400 foot long tunnel. He also has two of the
largest F scale trains in his museum that

00:00:25.510 --> 00:00:27.710
were build completely by hand, including all
of the scenery and background.

00:00:27.710 --> 00:00:33.860
Randall Rosenthal creates amazing wooden sculptures
that look like paper objects. All of his projects

00:00:33.860 --> 00:00:39.020
start from a single block of wood and are
hand-painted once carved. Some of his work

00:00:39.020 --> 00:00:45.690
includes a cardboard box full of cash, newspapers,
box full of baseball cards, and binders full

00:00:45.690 --> 00:00:46.740
of papers.

00:00:46.740 --> 00:00:52.360
Mister Finch is&nbsp;a self-taught artist that
sews nature-inspired original creations. They

00:00:52.360 --> 00:00:56.940
look similar to taxidermy and he uses recycled
materials to make them. Some of his works

00:00:56.940 --> 00:01:02.750
include Tea Making Spider, Halloween Hares,
and Felinka- a larger sculpture made from

00:01:02.750 --> 00:01:04.690
leather and fake fur.

00:01:04.690 --> 00:01:10.259
Brett Kern creates these hyper-realistic ceramic
sculptures that look like inflatable toys.

00:01:10.259 --> 00:01:15.930
The work ranges from inflatable dinosaurs
to balloons and a space man. He sells them

00:01:15.930 --> 00:01:20.999
on his etsy page and it takes at least a month
to handmake them to order.

00:01:20.999 --> 00:01:21.999
Draw it

00:01:21.999 --> 00:01:26.350
Emptied Gestures is a body art project by
Heather Hansen. Each life-sized drawing is

00:01:26.350 --> 00:01:31.499
created by holding charcoal in each hand and
making choreographed movements across the

00:01:31.499 --> 00:01:36.869
paper. She says she's looking for ways to
download her movement directly onto paper,

00:01:36.869 --> 00:01:39.640
emptying gestures from one form to another.

00:01:39.640 --> 00:01:45.141
Michael Mapes creates these intricate collage
portraits out of scientific specimens. He

00:01:45.141 --> 00:01:52.009
uses parts of photographic prints, glass vials,
insect pins, dried botanical matter, and other

00:01:52.009 --> 00:01:56.090
materials to create his works inspired by
Dutch painters.

00:01:56.090 --> 00:02:12.140
And now for some pieces from the Art of Tolkien
series by Jian Guo.

00:02:12.140 --> 00:02:17.129
BreakThru films is creating the world's first
feature length painted animation about the

00:02:17.129 --> 00:02:22.209
life of Vincent Van Gogh. It's told entirely
through his paintings and the characters in

00:02:22.209 --> 00:02:28.890
them. 56,800 paintings will be made by the
films 40 painters in order to create the finished

00:02:28.890 --> 00:02:29.890
piece.

